solutions.content:
Just ignore impossible cases before checking all conditions.
Time: `O(N^3)`
Space: `O(N)` for input `arr`
```
class Solution:
    def countGoodTriplets(self, arr: List[int], a: int, b: int, c: int) -> int:
        n, result = len(arr), 0
        for i in range(n):
            for k in range(i + 1, n):
                if abs(arr[i] - arr[k]) > c: continue
                result += sum(abs(arr[i] - arr[j]) <= a and abs(arr[j] - arr[k]) <= b
                              for j in range(i + 1, k))
        return result
```

