# Approach
ist we check the 
# # condition 1 **if(abs(nums[i]-nums[j])<=a)** 

if it satisfy the we will intialize the variable just greater than J and iterate i.e k=J+1 in 3rd for loop 
now  we will check for next two conditions 
 # CONDITION TWO AND THREE
# **if(abs(nums[k]-nums[j])<=b && abs(nums[k]-nums[i])<=c)**

if this becomes true we will increment the count variable 
which become our result

