In case of positive number we need to create max val (absolute), in case of negative we need to create min abs val. 

For positive we will put the number on max possible place value, we will skip all greater place values having value greater than the given integer. 

Example: `8934 to insert 5 we will make it 89534, skip 8, 9 since they are greater.`

We'll follow similar approach for negative numbers. (but in case of that we will form min number)

Example: `-113 to insert 2 we will create min 4 digit i.e 1123, skip first 2 1s since they are smaller than 2,  then append - in the start will give us -1123`

```
class Solution {
public:
    string maxValue(string s, int x) {
        bool neg = false;
        if(s[0]=='-') {
            neg = true;
            s.erase(0, 1);
        }

        int i = 0;
        char xc = x+'0';
        string ans = "";
        int n = s.length();

        while((i<n && s[i]<=xc && neg) || (i<n && s[i]>=xc && !neg)) {
            ans+=s[i];
            i++;
        }
        ans+=xc;
        while(i<n){
            ans+=s[i];
            i++;
        }

        if(neg) ans="-"+ans;
        return ans;  
    }
};
```

