# Intuition
Find the position of x to make the input maximum

# Approach
Iterate through the input from left to right and compare x with the number at each position. For positive numbers, we search for the first number less than x. For negative numbers, we search for the first number greater than x.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String maxValue(String n, int x) {
        // index where x should be inserted
        int i = 0;
        if (n.charAt(0) == '-') {
            i = 1;
            while (i < n.length() && n.charAt(i) - '0' <= x ) {
                i++;
            }   
        } else {
            i = 0;
            while (i < n.length() && n.charAt(i) - '0' >= x ) {
                i++;
            }
        }
        // insert x at the end
        if (i == n.length()) {
            return n + String.valueOf(x);
        }

        return n.substring(0, i) + String.valueOf(x) + n.substring(i);

    }
}
```

