# Intuition
Depending on whether the number is negative or positive (the given string), we will find the index to insert the given number i.e. x.

# Approach
For positive numbers, iterate from start i.e. index 0 till x is greater than the digit in the given number.
Reason we iterate from start is thatthe value of the place i.e. (1000th place then 100th place and so on) decreases from left to right or start to end so if we find the index where x is greater than digit at that index, then we will break the loop and insert x there.

For negative numbers iteration is started at 1 as first index is the '-' character than is non-numeric. Then here we have to minimise the positive part of the negative number. So we will iterate until x is less than the digit at that i'th index.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

