My initial thought to solve this problem is to loop through the string and check if the given x is greater or lesser than the current element. If it is greater, then replace the current element with x and return the string else continue to loop till the end of the string.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

I will be using the iterative approach to solve this problem. The idea is to loop through the given string, if it starts with a '-', then replace the current element with x if x is lesser than the current element, else if it does not start with a '-', then replace the current element with x if x is greater than the current element. If no such element is found, then append x to the end of the string and return the modified string.

