# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
If number is positive, we need to make the number as big as possible, and do the opposite for negative number.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We check the sign of the number first. If it has the '-' sign, then clearly it is negative, so we will try to make the nubmer as small as possible. We do that by going through all the digits of number and check if it is strictly more than our value for inserting **x**. If we find such value, we concatenate all the values before that character with our value **x**, and add the rest of the characters. If there is no such digit, and x is not less than any character in number, we add it to the end of the number.

As per positive number though, we go through all the characters and check if it is less than our value for inserting. If the character is less than **x**, we insert the value. Again, if there is no digit in number that is less than **x**, we concatenate the **x** to the end of the number.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) where n is the length of the number
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) where n is the length of the number
# Code
